snippet.textDisplay: Ross is absolutely right. A thirteen count isn’t a ten count. And btw, guys? Remember this: Deontay didn’t start boxing until he was TWENTY-ONE. That is INSANE. All the preposterous comments of a Tyson comparison are just that—preposterous. Look at Wilder. Imagine him having one of the great boxing trainers (Tyson’s Gus D’mato) taking him under his wing when he was THIRTEEN. What in the name of good God would he look like at Twenty-five? I’m sick of the negative comments about a guy who started boxing when the vast majority of guys have already had dozens of amateur bouts, if not having made their pro debuts. Let’s be real.
